[Student "S"]
{You have a textbook 1NT opener, so you open 1NT. Partner says 4NT.  

<b>THIS IS NOT BLACKWOOD</b>. Partner's bid is the Quantitative 4NT. He has 16 points and is inviting you to bid slam if you have a maximum opener, but to pass with a minimum. Since your 17 point hand is at the top of the 1NT range you accept the invitation and bid 6NT.}

